<div id="about-the-community" class="section-spacer">
    <h2 class="sect-title">About Sunnyside</h2>
    <div class="col-grid-2">
        <div>
            <p class="par-lg">The community of Sunnyside dates back to the first settlers in Calgary in the 1880’s, and was incorporated into the city itself in 1904, making it a rather historical set of land.</p>
            <p class="par-lg">Not only does the close proximity give residents much to do, Sunnyside is also located near Kensington, a trendy business and commercial district, focused at the intersection of 10th St. NW and Kensington Road.</p>
            <p class="par-lg">Broken Plate is a popular Greek restaurant chain in Calgary with a restaurant in Kensington, with Fast-Forward Magazine praising its classic Greek dishes and stylish, comfortable setting, going as far to say “doesn’t need fixing.”</p>
            <p class="par-lg">Schools located in Sunnyside include one public school operated by the CBE.</p>
            <p class="par-lg">Medical services are not hard to come by, with Foothills Hospital just down Memorial Drive, and various clinics in the Kensington district.</p>
            <p class="par-lg">Sunnyside Station services the community with C-train access, making easy transport around the city.</p>


